'''''Star Wars Manga: A New Hope''''' is a manga-style adaptation of the film [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']]. The series was illustrated by [[Hisao Tamaki]] and edited by [[David Land]], and was specifically adapted from the screenplay of the movie by [[George Lucas]]. It was, of course, based on the original story, though slight differences between the manga and the movie do occur.

Due to the fact that was an adaptation of the movie, it was treated in the same vein as the [[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' novelization]]. It enjoyed a level of canon only slightly lower than G-level canon, and took precedence over other titles within the franchise's [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]], though these titles are now considered part of the continuity of ''Star Wars'' Legends and are no longer considered [[canon]] except to the degree that they align with the events of the original film.

